Norma Mngoma was testifying at the state capture inquiry. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Nomachule Gigaba, estranged wife of former minister Malusi Gigaba responded to her husband's affidavit in which he described her testimony as blatant lies and total fabrication. She in turn has stood by her testimony that her husband was a frequent visitor to the Guptas and was under pressure to do their bidding. WATCH: Norma Mngoma back in the hot seat at state capture inquiry She says Gigaba kept her informed of his visits to the Guptas. Mngoma was testifying at the state capture inquiry.